"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-10-paris-2024-olympics-nigerias-last-medal-hope-reuben-crashes-out-in-wrestling\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's hope of winning a medal at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games went up in thin air after Hannah Reuben crashed out in the women's freestyle wrestling 76kg on Saturday.  Reuben lost 5-2 to Mongolia's Davaanasan Amar in their Round of 16 contest.  Her ouster capped a disastrous outing for Nigeria in Paris 2024.  It's the first time the country has failed to win a single medal at the Olympics since the 2012 edition hosted by London.  Much was expected from top athletes like Tobi Amusan, Ese Brume and Favour Ofili, but they failed to live up to the hype.  Team Nigeria will now return to the drawing board for the 2028 Olympic Games, which will be hosted by Los Angeles.  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  CAF Confederation Cup: El-Kanemi Warriors lament cost of playing in Ikenne  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Reuben launches Nigeria's final search for medal  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"